Re: DIS: Policy Settings

Kolja wrote:

>Crito:
>>>
>Why would reducing the batch size make any difference?
><<

>Because at the moment, with secrecy and no declarations of presence,
>we need at least 5 VTs to get any individual proposal through. And
>only some 10 VTs or so are entering circulation every week (at the
>moment, with hardly any farms operational). That's just enough for 2
>proposals, so if we aim at a constant no of VTs of circulation (and
>players have always tended to hoard VTs, so this is a conservative
>estimate) and you distribute three proposals per week, at least one of
>them is guaranteed to fail quorum.

>Which may not be a bad thing, mind you, but while it will mark the
>success of the current attepmts to get a meaningful economy going, it
>would also lead to attempts to water down scarcity again (as you,
>Crito, have suggested recently).

Fair enough.  However, there are a significant number of VTs already in
circulation.  I think I will leave the batch size at 3 for the moment.  This
might be an incentive for Players to get Plots going before the current
"excess" becomes too depleted.  It will be interesting to see if we can even
get *two* proposals passed in a batch anyway.  8)

-- Crito


